---
import '../styles/global.css';
---
<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <title>#My99Aravali | Save the Small Hills</title>
    <meta name="description" content="A 99-meter hill is still a hill. Join #My99Aravali to stop mining of the Aravalis under the ‘100-meter’ rule." />

    <meta property="og:title" content="Save the Aravalis" />
    <meta property="og:description" content="Nature doesn’t measure in meters. Join #My99Aravali to protect low ridges, groundwater, clean air, and wildlife corridors." />
    <meta property="og:type" content="website" />

    <link rel="icon" href="data:," />
    <!-- Google Analytics (Partytown Optimized). Replace G-XXXXXXXXXX with your Measurement ID. -->
    <script type="text/partytown" src="https://www.googletagmanager.com/gtag/js?id=G-T9RF3CM8PV"></script>
    <script type="text/partytown">
      window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
      function gtag(){dataLayer.push(arguments);}
      gtag('js', new Date());
      gtag('config', 'G-T9RF3CM8PV');
    </script>
  </head>
  <body class="min-h-screen">
    <header class="sticky top-0 z-50 backdrop-blur bg-black/25 border-b border-white/10">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-4 py-3 flex items-center justify-between gap-4">
        <a href="#top" class="flex items-center gap-3">
          <div class="h-9 w-9 rounded-xl bg-gradient-to-br from-aravali-brown to-aravali-sand border border-white/10 shadow-soft"></div>
          <div class="leading-tight">
            <div class="font-semibold tracking-tight">We are Aravali</div>
            <div class="text-xs text-white/70">#My99Aravali</div>
          </div>
        </a>

        <nav class="hidden md:flex items-center gap-6 text-sm text-white/80">
          <a class="hover:text-white" href="#problem">The 100-meter trap</a>
          <a class="hover:text-white font-semibold text-aravali-pink" href="#evidence">THE MAP</a>
          <a class="hover:text-white" href="#campaign">#My99Aravali</a>
          <a class="hover:text-white" href="#join">Join</a>
        </nav>
      </div>
    </header>

    <main id="top">
      <!-- START OF NEW MAP SECTION (now first) -->
      <section id="evidence" class="relative scroll-mt-20 border-y border-white/5 bg-black/20">
        <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-4 py-14 md:py-20">
          <div class="text-center max-w-3xl mx-auto mb-10">
            <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-semibold">We Mapped the Destruction.</h2>
            <p class="mt-4 text-lg text-white/75">
              NASA satellite data exposes more than 30% risk to the Aravalis, contradicting the minister's 2% claim. "WeAreAravali" demands a 100% mining ban.
            </p>
          </div>

          <!-- Custom Legend -->
          <div class="flex flex-wrap justify-center gap-4 mb-6 text-sm">
            <!-- Layer 1: Dark Green -->
            <div class="flex items-center gap-2 rounded-full border border-white/10 bg-white/5 px-4 py-2">
              <span class="block h-3 w-3 rounded-full bg-[#006400] shadow-[0_0_10px_#006400]"></span>
              <span class="text-white/90">Existing Reserved Area</span>
            </div>

            <!-- Layer 2: Neon Green -->
            <div class="flex items-center gap-2 rounded-full border border-green-500/30 bg-green-500/10 px-4 py-2">
              <span class="block h-3 w-3 rounded-full bg-[#00FF00] shadow-[0_0_10px_#00FF00]"></span>
              <span class="text-white/90 font-semibold">Added by the New Definition</span>
            </div>

            <!-- Layer 3: Red -->
            <div class="flex items-center gap-2 rounded-full border border-red-500/30 bg-red-500/10 px-4 py-2">
              <span class="block h-3 w-3 rounded-full bg-[#FF0000] shadow-[0_0_10px_#FF0000]"></span>
              <span class="text-white/90 font-semibold">LOSS (Unprotected)</span>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Single Map Container (Bristol FABDEM only) -->
          <div class="relative w-full h-[500px] md:h-[700px] overflow-hidden rounded-3xl border border-white/15 bg-black shadow-2xl">
            <!-- FABDEM MAP -->
            <iframe
              id="map-fabdem"
              class="absolute inset-0 w-full h-full"
              src="https://felt.com/embed/map/Getting-started-with-Felt-Cim1MjkPTiWPdbEgeoN2xA?loc=25.345%2C75.331%2C7.86z&legend=0&cooperativeGestures=1&link=1&geolocation=1&zoomControls=1&scaleBar=1"
              frameborder="0"
              title="FABDEM Map"
              referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin"
            ></iframe>
          </div>

          <!-- 3. CAPTION -->
          <div class="mt-4 text-center text-xs text-white/40">
            <span id="map-desc">
              Showing <strong>Bristol FABDEM</strong> data. Bare-earth model excluding vegetation (31.9% Loss).
            </span>
          </div>

          <!-- Data Citation -->
          <div class="mt-4 flex flex-col md:flex-row justify-between items-center text-xs text-white/40 gap-2">
            <div>Methodology: Geomorphic Relief Analysis (&gt;20m relief)</div>
          </div>

          <!-- Call to Action below map -->
          <div class="mt-8 text-center">
            <p class="text-white/80 mb-4">Is your village or favorite hill in the Red Zone?</p>
            <a href="#join" class="inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-xl bg-white/10 border border-white/10 px-5 py-2 text-sm font-semibold text-white hover:bg-white/20 transition-colors">
              Report a Threat
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>
      <!-- END OF NEW MAP SECTION -->

      <!-- PRESENTATION SECTION -->
      <section id="presentation" class="border-b border-white/5 bg-black/25">
        <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-4 py-10 md:py-14">
          <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-semibold text-center mb-6">Presentation</h2>
          <div class="mb-4 flex justify-end">
            <button
              id="presentation-fullscreen-toggle"
              type="button"
              class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-xl border border-white/20 bg-white/5 px-3 py-1.5 text-xs md:text-sm font-medium text-white/80 hover:bg-white/10 hover:text-white transition-colors"
            >
              <span>Full screen</span>
            </button>
          </div>

          <div id="presentation-container" class="relative w-full h-[500px] md:h-[700px] overflow-hidden rounded-3xl border border-white/15 bg-black shadow-2xl">
            <iframe
              src="https://gamma.app/embed/9wc6v6d8ipqinay"
              class="absolute inset-0 w-full h-full"
              style="border: 0;"
              allow="fullscreen"
              title="The Aravali Crisis: A Scientific Analysis of India's Vanishing Green Wall"
            ></iframe>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- SOURCES & METHODOLOGY (Collapsible) -->
      <section class="border-b border-white/5 bg-black/40 py-8">
        <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-4">
          <details class="group rounded-xl border border-white/10 bg-white/5 open:bg-black/40">
            <summary class="flex cursor-pointer items-center justify-between p-4 text-sm font-medium text-white/70 hover:text-white group-open:text-white">
              <span>View Data Sources & Government References</span>
              <span class="transition group-open:rotate-180">
                <svg fill="none" height="20" shape-rendering="geometricPrecision" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.5" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="20"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6"></path></svg>
              </span>
            </summary>
            <div class="border-t border-white/10 p-5 text-sm text-white/60">
              <div class="grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-1">
                <div>
                  <h4 class="font-semibold text-white mb-3">Forensic Data Analysis</h4>
                  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 text-sm text-white/70">
                    <!-- DATASET 1 -->
                    <div class="p-4 rounded-xl bg-white/5 border border-white/10">
                      <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
                        <div class="h-2 w-2 rounded-full bg-aravali-pink"></div>
                        <strong class="text-white">Primary: NASA SRTM</strong>
                      </div>
                      <ul class="list-disc pl-4 space-y-1 text-xs text-white/60">
                        <li><strong>Type:</strong> Digital Surface Model (DSM).</li>
                        <li><strong>What it sees:</strong> The true "Envelope" of the terrain, including rock, scrub, and vegetation height.</li>
                        <li><strong>Result:</strong> <span class="text-white font-bold">42.6% Area Lost.</span></li>
                      </ul>
                    </div>

                    <!-- DATASET 2 -->
                    <div class="p-4 rounded-xl bg-white/5 border border-white/10">
                      <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
                        <div class="h-2 w-2 rounded-full bg-blue-400"></div>
                        <strong class="text-white">Validation: Bristol FABDEM</strong>
                      </div>
                      <ul class="list-disc pl-4 space-y-1 text-xs text-white/60">
                        <li><strong>Type:</strong> Digital Terrain Model (DTM).</li>
                        <li><strong>What it sees:</strong> The "Bare Earth." It algorithmically removes trees/buildings to find the dirt underneath.</li>
                        <li><strong>Result:</strong> <span class="text-white font-bold">31.9% Area Lost.</span></li>
                      </ul>
                    </div>
                  </div>

                  <div class="mt-6 border-t border-white/10 pt-4">
                    <h4 class="font-semibold text-white mb-2">Sensitivity Analysis (Stress Testing)</h4>
                    <p class="text-sm text-white/70 mb-3">
                      To ensure accuracy, we compared multiple datasets. All confirm that a massive portion of the range is stripped of protection.
                    </p>

                    <div class="overflow-x-auto rounded-lg border border-white/10">
                      <table class="w-full text-sm text-left text-white/70">
                        <thead class="text-xs text-white/50 uppercase bg-white/5 border-b border-white/10">
                          <tr>
                            <th class="px-4 py-2">Dataset</th>
                            <th class="px-4 py-2 text-white">Area Lost</th>
                          </tr>
                        </thead>
                        <tbody>
                          <tr class="border-b border-white/5">
                            <td class="px-4 py-2">NASA SRTM (Standard)</td>
                            <td class="px-4 py-2 text-white font-mono">42.6%</td>
                          </tr>
                          <tr class="border-b border-white/5">
                            <td class="px-4 py-2">Bristol FABDEM (Conservative)</td>
                            <td class="px-4 py-2 text-white font-mono">32%</td>
                          </tr>
                          <tr>
                            <td class="px-4 py-2">ISRO (High-Resolution DEM)</td>
                            <td class="px-4 py-2 text-white font-mono">45%</td>
                          </tr>
                        </tbody>
                      </table>
                    </div>
                    
                    <p class="mt-3 text-xs text-white/50 italic">
                      *Conclusion: Even under the strictest, most conservative parameters (25m height, no vegetation), nearly 1/4th of the range is abandoned. The scientifically accurate model (20m + Volumetric) identifies 42.6% loss.
                    </p>
                  </div>

                  <div class="mt-6 border-t border-white/10 pt-4 text-xs text-white/60">
                    <h4 class="font-semibold text-white mb-2">Data License</h4>
                    <p>
                      This data is released under CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 (Attribution-NonCommercial-NoDerivatives).
                    </p>
                    <p class="mt-2">
                      You are free to share and embed this map for awareness. You may not download, modify, or sell the raw geospatial data without permission from WeAreAravali.org.
                    </p>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </details>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- HERO SECTION (now second) -->
      <section class="relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute inset-0 -z-20 bg-[url('/images/aravali_supremecourrt.png')] bg-cover bg-center opacity-40"></div>
        <div class="absolute inset-0 -z-10">
          <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-[radial-gradient(900px_500px_at_20%_10%,rgba(199,165,122,0.20),transparent_60%)]"></div>
          <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-[radial-gradient(900px_500px_at_80%_15%,rgba(229,107,131,0.18),transparent_55%)]"></div>
          <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-[linear-gradient(180deg,rgba(0,0,0,0.40)_0%,rgba(0,0,0,0.70)_45%,rgba(0,0,0,0.88)_100%)]"></div>
          <div class="absolute inset-0 opacity-35 [background-image:linear-gradient(to_right,rgba(255,255,255,0.06)_1px,transparent_1px),linear-gradient(to_bottom,rgba(255,255,255,0.06)_1px,transparent_1px)] [background-size:44px_44px]"></div>
        </div>

        <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-4 pt-12 pb-10 md:pt-16 md:pb-16 grid lg:grid-cols-[1.2fr_0.8fr] gap-10 items-start">
          <div>
            <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-full border border-white/15 bg-white/5 px-3 py-1 text-xs text-white/80">
              <span class="h-2 w-2 rounded-full bg-aravali-pink"></span>
              The 100-meter rule is a trap
            </div>

            <h1 class="mt-5 text-4xl md:text-6xl font-semibold tracking-tight">
              THIS HILL DOES NOT EXIST.
              <span class="block mt-3 text-white/80 text-2xl md:text-3xl font-medium">It is 99 meters tall. The new definition says it must be 100 meters to be saved.</span>
            </h1>

            <p class="mt-5 text-base md:text-lg text-white/75 max-w-2xl">
              Because it is “too short,” this hill—and most of the Aravali ridges—can be treated as mineable land.
              <span class="text-white">We say: Nature doesn’t measure in meters.</span>
            </p>

            <div class="mt-10 grid sm:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
              <div class="rounded-2xl border border-white/10 bg-gradient-to-br from-aravali-earth/70 to-black/40 p-4">
                <div class="text-sm text-white/70">100 meters or higher</div>
                <div class="mt-1 text-xl font-semibold">Protected hill</div>
                <div class="mt-2 text-sm text-white/70">It is a “hill.” It gets protected.</div>
              </div>
              <div class="rounded-2xl border border-white/10 bg-gradient-to-br from-aravali-brown/70 to-black/40 p-4">
                <div class="text-sm text-white/70">99 meters or lower</div>
                <div class="mt-1 text-xl font-semibold">Mineable land</div>
                <div class="mt-2 text-sm text-white/70">It is treated as “flat land.” It gets mined.</div>
              </div>
              <div class="rounded-2xl border border-white/10 bg-gradient-to-br from-aravali-green/70 to-black/40 p-4">
                <div class="text-sm text-white/70">The danger</div>
                <div class="mt-1 text-xl font-semibold">We lose everything</div>
                <div class="mt-2 text-sm text-white/70">Water. Clean air. Wildlife corridors.</div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <aside class="lg:sticky lg:top-24">
            <div id="join" class="rounded-3xl border border-white/12 bg-black/35 p-6 shadow-soft">
              <div class="text-sm text-white/70">Sign up</div>
              <h2 class="mt-2 text-2xl font-semibold">Count Me In.</h2>
              <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-white/75">I will fight for the 99 meters.</p>

              <form
                id="joinForm"
                class="mt-5 grid gap-3"
                name="supporters"
                method="POST"
                data-netlify="true"
                netlify-honeypot="bot-field"
                action="/"
              >
                <input type="hidden" name="form-name" value="supporters" />
                <p class="hidden">
                  <label>
                    Don’t fill this out if you’re human: <input name="bot-field" />
                  </label>
                </p>

                <label class="grid gap-1">
                  <span class="text-sm text-white/80">Full Name *</span>
                  <input
                    class="w-full rounded-xl border border-white/15 bg-white/5 px-4 py-3 text-white placeholder:text-white/40"
                    type="text"
                    name="fullName"
                    autocomplete="name"
                    required
                    placeholder="Your name"
                  />
                </label>

                <label class="grid gap-1">
                  <span class="text-sm text-white/80">Mobile Number *</span>
                  <input
                    class="w-full rounded-xl border border-white/15 bg-white/5 px-4 py-3 text-white placeholder:text-white/40"
                    type="tel"
                    name="mobile"
                    inputmode="numeric"
                    autocomplete="tel"
                    required
                    pattern="[0-9]{10}"
                    placeholder="Phone (WhatsApp)"
                    aria-describedby="mobileHelp"
                  />
                  <span id="mobileHelp" class="text-xs text-white/55">Use a 10-digit Indian mobile number (digits only).</span>
                </label>

                <label class="grid gap-1">
                  <span class="text-sm text-white/80">Email (optional)</span>
                  <input
                    class="w-full rounded-xl border border-white/15 bg-white/5 px-4 py-3 text-white placeholder:text-white/40"
                    type="email"
                    name="email"
                    autocomplete="email"
                    placeholder="you@example.com"
                  />
                </label>

                <div class="mt-2 grid gap-2">
                  <label class="flex items-start gap-3 text-sm text-white/80">
                    <input class="mt-1 h-4 w-4 rounded border-white/30 bg-white/5" type="checkbox" name="pledge_protest" value="yes" />
                    <span>Come to the SAKA.</span>
                  </label>
                  <label class="flex items-start gap-3 text-sm text-white/80">
                    <input class="mt-1 h-4 w-4 rounded border-white/30 bg-white/5" type="checkbox" name="pledge_post" value="yes" />
                    <span>Post a <span class="font-semibold">#My99Aravali</span> photo today.</span>
                  </label>
                  <label class="flex items-start gap-3 text-sm text-white/80">
                    <input class="mt-1 h-4 w-4 rounded border-white/30 bg-white/5" type="checkbox" name="pledge_friend" value="yes" />
                    <span>Bring a friend.</span>
                  </label>
                </div>

                <button 
                  id="submitBtn"
                  type="submit" 
                  class="mt-3 inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-xl bg-aravali-pink px-5 py-3 font-semibold text-white shadow-soft hover:brightness-110 active:brightness-95 disabled:opacity-70 disabled:cursor-not-allowed"
                >
                  <span id="btnText">Join the Movement</span>
                  <!-- Hidden Spinner -->
                  <svg id="btnSpinner" class="hidden h-5 w-5 animate-spin text-white ml-2" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                    <circle class="opacity-25" cx="12" cy="12" r="10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="4"></circle>
                    <path class="opacity-75" fill="currentColor" d="M4 12a8 8 0 018-8V0C5.373 0 0 5.373 0 12h4zm2 5.291A7.962 7.962 0 014 12H0c0 3.042 1.135 5.824 3 7.938l3-2.647z"></path>
                  </svg>
                </button>

                <div class="text-xs text-white/55">
                  Your details will only be used for Aravali conservation alerts and will not be shared.
                </div>
              </form>
            </div>
          </aside>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section id="problem" class="relative">
        <div class="absolute inset-0 -z-10 bg-[linear-gradient(180deg,rgba(229,107,131,0.08)_0%,rgba(0,0,0,0)_40%)]"></div>
        <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-4 py-14 md:py-20">
          <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-[1fr_1fr] gap-10 items-start">
            <div>
              <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-semibold">The “100-Meter Trap”</h2>
              <p class="mt-4 text-white/75">Here is what the new Supreme Court ruling means for you:</p>

              <div class="mt-6 grid gap-4">
                <div class="rounded-2xl border border-white/10 bg-gradient-to-br from-aravali-earth/70 to-black/40 p-5">
                  <div class="font-semibold">100 Meters or Higher</div>
                  <div class="mt-1 text-sm text-white/70">It is a “Hill.” It gets protected.</div>
                </div>
                <div class="rounded-2xl border border-white/10 bg-gradient-to-br from-aravali-brown/70 to-black/40 p-5">
                  <div class="font-semibold">99 Meters or Lower</div>
                  <div class="mt-1 text-sm text-white/70">It is “Flat Land.” It gets mined.</div>
                </div>
              </div>

              <div class="mt-6 rounded-2xl border border-white/10 bg-black/25 p-6">
                <div class="font-semibold">The Danger</div>
                <div class="mt-2 text-sm text-white/75">
                  Most of the Aravalis that hold our groundwater and block the desert dust are low ridges. They are under 100 meters.
                  If we follow this rule, we lose our water, our clean air, and our wildlife corridors.
                </div>
              </div>

              <div class="mt-6 rounded-2xl border border-aravali-pink/25 bg-aravali-pink/10 p-6">
                <div class="font-semibold">But we have one chance left.</div>
                <div class="mt-2 text-sm text-white/75">
                  The only acceptable plan is Total Preservation. We refuse to negotiate on which hills live or die.
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="rounded-3xl border border-white/10 bg-gradient-to-b from-white/10 to-white/5 p-6">
              <div class="mt-3 grid gap-4">
                <figure class="aspect-[16/10] overflow-hidden rounded-2xl border border-white/10 bg-black/40">
                  <img
                    src="/images/aravali_supremecourrt.png"
                    alt="Supreme Court related Aravali protection visual"
                    class="h-full w-full object-cover"
                    loading="lazy"
                  />
                </figure>
                <figure class="aspect-[16/10] overflow-hidden rounded-2xl border border-white/10 bg-black/40">
                  <img
                    src="/images/contour.png"
                    alt="Contour graphic tracing the Aravali ridge across Rajasthan"
                    class="h-full w-full object-contain"
                    loading="lazy"
                  />
                </figure>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section id="campaign" class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-4 py-14 md:py-20">
        <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-[1fr_1fr] gap-10 items-start">
          <div>
            <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-semibold">Show Them What We Will Lose.</h2>
            <p class="mt-4 text-white/75">
              The government thinks these low hills are just “wasteland.” Prove them wrong.
              We are launching <span class="font-semibold">#My99Aravali</span>. We need you to take a photo of the small, local hills near your home that are at risk.
            </p>

            <div class="mt-6 rounded-3xl border border-white/10 bg-white/5 p-6">
              <div class="text-sm text-white/70">How to join</div>
              <div class="mt-4 grid gap-4">
                <div class="rounded-2xl border border-white/10 bg-black/25 p-5">
                  <div class="font-semibold">1. Find a Hill</div>
                  <div class="mt-1 text-sm text-white/70">Go to a ridge or small hill near you (one that looks “too short” to be a mountain).</div>
                </div>
                <div class="rounded-2xl border border-white/10 bg-black/25 p-5">
                  <div class="font-semibold">2. Snap a Photo</div>
                  <div class="mt-1 text-sm text-white/70">Capture the trees, the animals, or the view.</div>
                </div>
                <div class="rounded-2xl border border-white/10 bg-black/25 p-5">
                  <div class="font-semibold">3. Post It</div>
                  <div class="mt-1 text-sm text-white/70">Share on X/Twitter or Instagram with this caption:</div>
                  <div class="mt-3 rounded-2xl border border-white/10 bg-black/35 p-4 text-sm text-white/80">
                    “This is #My99Aravali. It might be short, but it gives us oxygen. Don't mine it just because it's under 100m. @moefcc #SaveAravali”
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="rounded-3xl border border-white/10 bg-gradient-to-b from-white/10 to-white/5 p-6">
            <div class="text-sm text-white/70">#My99Aravali photo wall</div>
            <div class="mt-4 grid grid-cols-2 gap-3">
              <figure class="aspect-[4/3] overflow-hidden rounded-2xl border border-white/10 bg-black/40">
